The paper discusses meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that focuses on building sample-efficient learning systems. The paper specifically studies the learning dynamics of LSTM Meta-Learners on three sets of structured tasks, which suggests that it falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the findings for research areas such as safety, curriculum design, and human-in-the-loop machine learning, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and learning (cs.LO).
